# 🟢 **SECTION 1 — BASICS OF EXCEL**
### 📘 Data Entry • Formatting • Essential Functions

---

# 📘 Introduction to Excel

**Step 1 — What is Excel?** <!-- .element: .fragment -->  
Microsoft Excel is a spreadsheet program to store, organize, and analyze data.

**Step 2 — Understanding the Interface**  
- **Ribbon** — Toolbar with tabs like Home, Insert, Page Layout <!-- .element: .fragment -->
- **Workbook** — File containing sheets <!-- .element: .fragment -->
- **Worksheet** — Single spreadsheet in a workbook <!-- .element: .fragment -->
- **Cells** — Intersection of row & column (e.g., A1) <!-- .element: .fragment -->
- **Formula Bar** — Where formulas are typed <!-- .element: .fragment -->

📷 *[Screenshot: Excel interface labeled]*  

💡 **Tip:** Save often — <kbd>Ctrl</kbd> + <kbd>S</kbd>

---

# ✏️ Basic Functions & Formatting

**Step 1 — Data Entry** <!-- .element: .fragment -->  
- Click cell → Type → Press <kbd>Enter</kbd> <!-- .element: .fragment -->

**Step 2 — Formatting**  
- Home → Font → Change style, color, size <!-- .element: .fragment -->
- Use Borders & Fill Color for emphasis <!-- .element: .fragment -->

**Step 3 — Number Formats**  
- Currency 💲 • Percentage % • Date 📅 <!-- .element: .fragment -->

**Step 4 — Basic Functions**  
- =SUM(A1:A10) ➕ Add values <!-- .element: .fragment -->
- =AVERAGE(A1:A10) 📊 Mean <!-- .element: .fragment -->
- =MIN(A1:A10) / =MAX(A1:A10) 🔻🔺 <!-- .element: .fragment -->

📷 *[Screenshot: Formatting toolbar]*

---

# 🗂 Data Management Tools

**Step 1 — Sort** <!-- .element: .fragment -->  
- Data → Sort A-Z / Z-A <!-- .element: .fragment -->

**Step 2 — Filter**  
- Data → Filter → Dropdown arrows <!-- .element: .fragment -->

**Step 3 — Find & Replace**  
- <kbd>Ctrl</kbd> + <kbd>H</kbd> <!-- .element: .fragment -->

**Step 4 — Data Validation**  
- Data → Data Validation → Dropdown list <!-- .element: .fragment -->

📷 *[Screenshot: Sort/Filter menu]*

---

# 🟡 **SECTION 2 — INTERMEDIATE EXCEL**
### 🧩 Formulas • Charts • PivotTables

---

# 🧩 Intermediate Formulas

**Step 1 — Text Functions** <!-- .element: .fragment -->  
- =LEFT(A1,4) — First 4 chars <!-- .element: .fragment -->
- =RIGHT(A1,3) — Last 3 chars <!-- .element: .fragment -->
- =MID(A1,3,5) — From 3rd position <!-- .element: .fragment -->

**Step 2 — Logical**  
- =IF(A2>100,"Pass","Fail") <!-- .element: .fragment -->

**Step 3 — Lookup**  
- =VLOOKUP("Apple",A2:C10,2,FALSE) <!-- .element: .fragment -->
- =XLOOKUP("Apple",A2:A10,B2:B10) <!-- .element: .fragment -->

📷 *[Screenshot: Formula example]*

---

# 📊 Charts & Visualization

**Step 1 — Select Data** <!-- .element: .fragment -->  
- Highlight table <!-- .element: .fragment -->

**Step 2 — Insert Chart**  
- Insert → Choose type <!-- .element: .fragment -->

**Step 3 — Format Chart**  
- Add titles, labels, legends <!-- .element: .fragment -->

**Step 4 — Conditional Formatting**  
- Home → Conditional Formatting → Set rules <!-- .element: .fragment -->

📷 *[Screenshot: Chart example]*

---

# 📈 PivotTables & PivotCharts

**Step 1 — Create** <!-- .element: .fragment -->  
- Insert → PivotTable <!-- .element: .fragment -->

**Step 2 — Build**  
- Drag to Rows, Columns, Values, Filters <!-- .element: .fragment -->

**Step 3 — PivotChart**  
- Analyze → PivotChart <!-- .element: .fragment -->

**Step 4 — Group**  
- By Month, Year, Category <!-- .element: .fragment -->

📷 *[Screenshot: PivotTable example]*

---

# 🔵 **SECTION 3 — ADVANCED EXCEL**
### 🧠 Power Formulas • Macros • Automation

---

# 🧠 Advanced Formulas

**Step 1 — INDEX & MATCH** <!-- .element: .fragment -->  
- =INDEX(B2:B10, MATCH("Product A",A2:A10,0)) <!-- .element: .fragment -->

**Step 2 — INDIRECT**  
- =INDIRECT("B"&5) <!-- .element: .fragment -->

**Step 3 — OFFSET**  
- =OFFSET(A1,1,2) <!-- .element: .fragment -->

**Step 4 — Array**  
- {=A1:A3*B1:B3} <!-- .element: .fragment -->

📷 *[Screenshot: INDEX & MATCH]*

---

# 🤖 Macros & VBA Basics

**Step 1 — Record** <!-- .element: .fragment -->  
- View → Macros → Record <!-- .element: .fragment -->

**Step 2 — Perform**  
- Format → Stop Recording <!-- .element: .fragment -->

**Step 3 — Run**  
- View → Macros → Run <!-- .element: .fragment -->

**Step 4 — VBA Editor**  
- <kbd>Alt</kbd> + <kbd>F11</kbd> <!-- .element: .fragment -->

📷 *[Screenshot: Macro Recorder]*

---

# 🔍 Power Query & Data Analysis

**Step 1 — Open** <!-- .element: .fragment -->  
- Data → Get & Transform <!-- .element: .fragment -->

**Step 2 — Clean**  
- Remove duplicates, fix data types <!-- .element: .fragment -->

**Step 3 — Merge**  
- Merge Queries <!-- .element: .fragment -->

**Step 4 — What-If**  
- Scenario Manager / Goal Seek <!-- .element: .fragment -->

